  <script type="text/javascript">
   jQuery(document).ready(function() {
				// CUSTOM AJAX CONTENT LOADING FUNCTION
				var ajaxRevslider = function(obj) {
				
					// obj.type : Post Type
					// obj.id : ID of Content to Load
					// obj.aspectratio : The Aspect Ratio of the Container / Media
					// obj.selector : The Container Selector where the Content of Ajax will be injected. It is done via the Essential Grid on Return of Content
					
					var content = "";

					data = {};
					
					data.action = 'revslider_ajax_call_front';
					data.client_action = 'get_slider_html';
					data.token = '38829ad7b0';
					data.type = obj.type;
					data.id = obj.id;
					data.aspectratio = obj.aspectratio;
					
					// SYNC AJAX REQUEST
					jQuery.ajax({
						type:"post",
						url:"https://www.flagspin.com/wp-admin/admin-ajax.php",
						dataType: 'json',
						data:data,
						async:false,
						success: function(ret, textStatus, XMLHttpRequest) {
							if(ret.success == true)
								content = ret.data;								
						},
						error: function(e) {
							console.log(e);
						}
					});
					
					 // FIRST RETURN THE CONTENT WHEN IT IS LOADED !!
					 return content;						 
				};
				
				// CUSTOM AJAX FUNCTION TO REMOVE THE SLIDER
				var ajaxRemoveRevslider = function(obj) {
					return jQuery(obj.selector+" .rev_slider").revkill();
				};

				// EXTEND THE AJAX CONTENT LOADING TYPES WITH TYPE AND FUNCTION
				var extendessential = setInterval(function() {
					if (jQuery.fn.tpessential != undefined) {
						clearInterval(extendessential);
						if(typeof(jQuery.fn.tpessential.defaults) !== 'undefined') {
							jQuery.fn.tpessential.defaults.ajaxTypes.push({type:"revslider",func:ajaxRevslider,killfunc:ajaxRemoveRevslider,openAnimationSpeed:0.3});   
							// type:  Name of the Post to load via Ajax into the Essential Grid Ajax Container
							// func: the Function Name which is Called once the Item with the Post Type has been clicked
							// killfunc: function to kill in case the Ajax Window going to be removed (before Remove function !
							// openAnimationSpeed: how quick the Ajax Content window should be animated (default is 0.3)
						}
					}
				},30);
			});
  </script>

         <script type="text/javascript">
          jQuery(document).ready(function(){
							"use strict";
							
							var _search_obj = jQuery("#header .header-bottom.v1 .header_search .bt_search");
							var _search_box = jQuery("#header .header-bottom.v1 .header_search");
							_search_obj.click(function(){
								var _windowWidth = jQuery('body').innerWidth();
								if(_windowWidth &lt; 1199 &amp;&amp; _windowWidth &gt; 700 )
								{
									if(_search_obj.hasClass("search_open")){
										_search_obj.removeClass("search_open").addClass("search_close");
										_search_box.css("overflow","hidden");
										_search_box.find("form").css("height","0");
									}
									else if(_search_obj.hasClass("search_close")){
										_search_obj.removeClass("search_close").addClass("search_open");
										_search_box.css("overflow","visible");
										_search_box.find("form").css("height","52px");
									}
								}
							});
							
							var _search_obj_v5 = jQuery("#header .header-bottom.v5 .header_search .bt_search");
							var _search_box_v5 = jQuery("#header .header-bottom.v5 .header_search");
							_search_obj_v5.click(function(){
								var _windowWidth = jQuery('body').innerWidth();
								if(_windowWidth &lt; 1199 &amp;&amp; _windowWidth &gt; 700 )
								{
									if(_search_obj_v5.hasClass("search_open")){
										_search_obj_v5.removeClass("search_open").addClass("search_close");
										_search_box_v5.css("overflow","hidden");
										_search_box_v5.find("form").css("height","0");
									}
									else if(_search_obj_v5.hasClass("search_close")){
										_search_obj_v5.removeClass("search_close").addClass("search_open");
										_search_box_v5.css("overflow","visible");
										_search_box_v5.find("form").css("height","52px");
									}
								}
							});
						});
         </script>

           <article class="post-3736 tribe_events type-tribe_events status-publish has-post-thumbnail tag-5v5 tag-mexico tribe_events_cat-5man tribe_events_cat-flag-football-combines tribe_events_cat-flag-football-tournaments cat_5man cat_flag-football-combines cat_flag-football-tournaments" id="post-3736">
            <div class="entry-content-post">
             <div class="tribe-no-js" data-category="" data-datepicker_format="0" data-live_ajax="1" id="tribe-events">
              <div class="tribe-events-before-html">

              <span class="tribe-events-ajax-loading">
               <img alt="Loading Events" class="tribe-events-spinner-medium" src="https://flagspin-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/plugins/the-events-calendar/src/resources/images/tribe-loading.gif"/>

               <h2 class="tribe-events-single-event-title summary entry-title">
                INTERNATIONAL FLAG FOOTBALL TOURNAMENT CARIBEAN BOWL, CANCN MXICO
               </h2>
               <div class="tribe-events-schedule updated published tribe-clearfix">
                <h3>
                 <span class="date-start dtstart">
                  April 17 @ 2:00 pm
                  <span class="value-title" title="2015-04-17UTC02:00">
                  </span>
                 </span>
                 -
                 <span class="date-end dtend">
                  April 19 @ 2:00 pm
                  <span class="value-title" title="2015-04-19UTC02:00">
                  </span>
                 </span>
                </h3>
                <span class="tribe-events-divider">
                 |
                </span>
                <span class="tribe-events-cost">
                 $250.00
                </span>
               </div>
               <!-- Event header -->
               <div data-title="INTERNATIONAL FLAG FOOTBALL TOURNAMENT CARIBEAN BOWL, CANCN MXICO - FlagSpin" flagspin="" id="tribe-events-header">
                <!-- Navigation -->

               <div class="post-3736 tribe_events type-tribe_events status-publish has-post-thumbnail tag-5v5 tag-mexico tribe_events_cat-5man tribe_events_cat-flag-football-combines tribe_events_cat-flag-football-tournaments cat_5man cat_flag-football-combines cat_flag-football-tournaments" id="post-3736">
                <!-- Event featured image, but exclude link -->
                <div class="tribe-events-event-image">
                 <img alt="INTERNATIONAL FLAG FOOTBALL TOURNAMENT CARIBEAN BOWL, CANCN MXICO" class="attachment-full wp-post-image" data-lazy-src="https://flagspin-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/flayeringlespatrocinadores.jpg" height="960" src="https://flagspin-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/plugins/speed-booster-pack/inc/images/1x1.trans.gif" title="INTERNATIONAL FLAG FOOTBALL TOURNAMENT CARIBEAN BOWL, CANCN MXICO photo" width="621"/>
                 <noscript>
                  <img alt="INTERNATIONAL FLAG FOOTBALL TOURNAMENT CARIBEAN BOWL, CANCN MXICO" class="attachment-full wp-post-image" height="960" src="https://flagspin-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/flayeringlespatrocinadores.jpg" title="INTERNATIONAL FLAG FOOTBALL TOURNAMENT CARIBEAN BOWL, CANCN MXICO photo" width="621"/>
                 </noscript>
                </div>
                <!-- Event content -->
                <div class="tribe-events-single-event-description tribe-events-content entry-content description">
                 <p>
                  This year will be held the International 5v5 Flag Football Tournament in Cancun , Quintana Roo, Mexico, taking Headquarters games the  COLISEO MAYA  field house  LIONS  ANAHUAC UNIVERSITY CANCUN , this tournament will perform from April 17th to 19th,2015
                  <strong>
                   MISSION
                  </strong>
                  ESTABLISH VALUES AND DISCIPLINE THROUGH FLAG FOOTBALL. FOSTERING A COMBINATION OF MULTICULTURAL INTERACTION AND BENEFITS FOR OUR YOUTH AND THE GENERAL COMMUNITY, THE FOUNDATION FOR WHICH IS BASED ON RESPECT, SPORTSMANSHIP, AND CAMARADERIE. PARTICIPATING COUNTRIES WE ARE ANTICIPATING 18 DIFFERENT MEXICAN STATES, 6 LOCAL TEAMS AND INVITED COUNTRIES. INVITED COUNTRIES ARE AS FOLLOWS: SPAIN, ITALY, CANADA, USA, DENMARK, GERMANY, ISRAEL, ARGENTINA, VENEZUELA, BRAZIL, GUATEMALA, COLOMBIA, AND CHILE.
                  <strong>
                   STYLE OF PLAY
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   5 ON 5 FLAG FOOTBALL
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   RANGES &amp; CATEGORIES
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   OPEN DIVISION
                  </strong>
                 </p>
                 <ul>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    MENS
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    MIXED
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    WOMENS
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                 </ul>
                 <p>
                  <strong>
                   FEMALE YOUTH TEAMS
                  </strong>
                 </p>
                 <ul>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    JUNIOR 12-14
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    JUNIOR VARSITY 15-17
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                 </ul>
                 <p>
                  <strong>
                   REQUIREMENTS
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   INSCRIPTION FEE OF $250.00USD FOR EACH TEAM
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   TO CONFIRM PARTICIPATION DUE BY THE 17 OF MARCH. SEND REGISTRATION FORMS AND ROSTER F-1R AND WIRE TRANSFER VOUCHER BY THE 17 OF MARCH.
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   IS MANDATORY THAT EACH PLAYER HAS INSURANCE (
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   ITS THE RESPONSIBILITY OF EACH TEAM
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   )
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   INSCRIPTION INCLUDES
                  </strong>
                 </p>
                 <ul>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    3 GAMES, HYDRATION
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    OFFICIATING
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    FIRST AID SERVICE
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    AMBULANCE, AWARDS
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    MUSIC AT THE FIELD
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    T-SHIRTS &amp; BACK PACKS FOR ALL PARTICIPANTS
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                 </ul>
                 <p>
                  <strong>
                   COMPETITION SYSTEM
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   3 QUALIFYING ROUNDS, PLUS WILDCARD, PLAYOFF, AND BOTH SEMIFINAL &amp; FINAL ROUNDS.
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   UNIFORMS
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   ALL TEAMS ARE REQUIRED TO PRESENT OFFICIAL UNIFORMS WITH NUMBERS ON BOTH THE FRONT AND BACK, IN ADDITION TO THEIR FLAGS. SUNGLASSES, POCKETS, CORDS, ETC., ARE NOT PERMITTED TO AVOID INJURY.
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   EACH FOREIGNER SHOULD HAVE THEIR COUNTRIES FLAG (75CM X 75CM) ALONG WITH THEIR NATIONAL ANTHEM FOR THE OPENING CEREMONY.
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   NATIONAL TEAMS NEED TO BRING THE TEAM FLAG WITH LOGO OR THEIR STATE FLAG (75CM X 75CM)
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   ALL PARTICIPANTS NEED TO BE PRESENT AT WELCOME PARTY WITH T-SHIRTS AND SOUVENIRS FROM THEIR TEAM TO EXCHANGE WITH OTHER PLAYERS. IF NECESSARY PULLOVERS WILL BE AVAILABLE IF TWO TEAMS HAVE THE SAME COLOR JERSEY
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   EACH TEAM WILL NEED TO PRESENT A GAME BALL: WOMENS- CF-6, MENS-1001, YOUTH-TDJ.
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   ALL PLAYERS, COACHES, STAFF, OFFICIALS, AND PARTICIPANTS NEED TO FOLLOW THE CODE OF CONDUCT WITHOUT EXCEPTION. SPORTSMANSHIP, RESPECT, AND CAMARADERIE ARE THE SPIRIT OF THIS EVENT.
                  </strong>
                  <strong>
                   AWARDS
                  </strong>
                 </p>
                 <ul>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    1
                    <sup>
                     ST
                    </sup>
                    PLACE TROPHY AND CHAMPIONSHIP T-SHIRTS
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    2
                    <sup>
                     ND
                    </sup>
                    PLACE MEDALS AND RUNNERUP T-SHIRTS
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    MVP AWARDS
                   </strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                   <strong>
                    SPECIAL RECOGNITION FOR COACHES
                   </strong>
                   .
                  </li>
                 </ul>
                 <p>
                  <b>
                   <span style="font-size: x-large">
                    OUR AWARD CEREMONY WILL BE ON SEOR FROGS CANCN
                   </span>
                  </b>
                 </p>
                </div>
                <!-- .tribe-events-single-event-description -->
                <div class="tribe-events-cal-links">
